In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act creating special funds for the division of fisheries and wildlife.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 131 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by adding the following section:-
3 Section 2D. There shall be established and set up on the books of the commonwealth a
4 separate, non-budgeted special revenue fund to be known as the MassWildlife Inland Fisheries
5 and Wildlife Mitigation and Enhancement Fund, which shall be administered by the director of
6 the division of fisheries and wildlife. There shall be credited into the fund revenues or other
7 financing sources directed to the fund by appropriation or other monies authorized by the general
8 court and specifically designated to be credited to the fund, monies received on account of
9 certifications, permits, licenses, authorizations, approvals, judgments, and agreements to address
10 adverse impacts to inland fish and wildlife resources, any income derived from the investment of
11 amounts credited to the fund and monies from the repayment of loans from the fund, funds from
12 public or private sources including, but not limited to, gifts, federal, state, or private grants,
1 of 4

13 donations, rebates and settlements received by the commonwealth that are specifically
14 designated to be credited to the fund and all other amounts credited or transferred into the fund
15 from any other source. The amounts credited to the fund shall be expended, without further
16 appropriation, for the purposes of protecting, mitigating damages to, studying and enhancing
17 inland fish and wildlife resources, in accordance with the terms of the certifications, permits,
18 licenses, authorizations, approvals, judgments, or agreements for which such amounts were
19 received.
20 Any unexpended balance in the fund at the end of a fiscal year shall remain in the fund
21 and available for expenditure in subsequent fiscal years and shall not revert to the general fund.
22 The state treasurer shall not deposit or transfer any amounts credited to the fund to the General
23 Fund or to any other fund other than the MassWildlife Inland Fisheries and Wildlife Mitigation
24 and Enhancement Fund. The director of the division of fisheries and wildlife shall not make
25 expenditures from this fund or take any other action so as to cause the fund to be deficient at any
26 point during the fiscal year. The state treasurer shall receive and deposit all revenues transmitted
27 to the state treasurer under the provisions of this section in such manner that will ensure the
28 highest rate of interest available consistent with the safety of the fund, and in an account from
29 which amounts may be withdrawn at any time without penalty for such withdrawal, all interest
30 accrued shall be deposited into the fund.
31 SECTION 2. Chapter 131A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official
32 Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following section:-
33 Section 8. There shall be established and set up on the books of the commonwealth a
34 separate, non-budgeted special revenue fund to be known as the Natural Heritage Mitigation
