35 Fund, which shall be administered by the director of the division of fisheries and wildlife acting
36 through the natural heritage and endangered species program. There shall be credited into the
37 fund revenues or other financing sources directed to the fund by appropriation or other monies
38 authorized by the general court and specifically designated to be credited to the fund, monies
39 required by the conditions of conservation and management permits issued pursuant to chapter
40 131A, monies received on account of certifications, permits, licenses, authorizations, approvals,
41 judgments, and agreements to address unavoidable adverse impacts to a species, any income
42 derived from the investment of amounts credited to the fund and monies from the repayment of
43 loans from the fund, funds from public or private sources including, but not limited to, gifts,
44 federal, state, or private grants, donations, rebates and settlements received by the
45 commonwealth that are specifically designated to be credited to the fund and all other amounts
46 credited or transferred into the fund from any other source. The amounts credited to the fund
47 shall be expended, without further appropriation, for the purposes of mitigating adverse impacts
48 to endangered, threatened, and special concern species, including but not limited to, habitat
49 management, research and the protection of land, and in accordance with the terms of the
50 certifications, permits, licenses, authorizations, approvals, judgments, or agreements for which
51 such amounts were received.
52 Any unexpended balance in the fund at the end of a fiscal year shall remain in the fund
53 and available for expenditure in subsequent fiscal years and shall not revert to the general fund.
54 The state treasurer shall not deposit or transfer any amounts credited to the fund to the general
55 fund or to any other fund other than the Natural Heritage Mitigation Fund. The director of the
56 division of fisheries and wildlife shall not make expenditures from this fund or take any other
57 action so as to cause the fund to be deficient at any point during the fiscal year, nor shall these
